Zambian President Sata Orders Extension of Mineral Exploration

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-10-09T14:42:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-09/zambian-president-sata-orders-extension-of-mineral-exploration.html
     Oct. 9 (Bloomberg) --Zambian President  Michael Sata  ordered
the Geological Survey Department to immediately extend mineral
exploration to parts of the Copperbelt province, according to
The Post.  Sata wants to boost earnings from copper and other minerals
in order to reduce poverty, the Lusaka newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka at 
 amukwita1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  